      "flexibility": "fixed",
      "default_duration_minutes": 480,
      "can_recur": true,
      "protected": true,
      "biblical_foundation": "Daily renewal, Sabbath rest. 'His mercies are new every morning' (Lamentations 3:23), 'Come away and rest a while' (Mark 6:31)",
      "notes": "Rest is commanded, not negotiable. Includes sleep, Sabbath, and restoration. Identity in God, not outputs."
    },
    {
      "id": "collaboration",
      "name": "Partnership Work",
      "description": "Covenant partnership - working together in genuine collaboration and mutual service",
      "priority": "high",
      "flexibility": "moveable",
      "default_duration_minutes": 90,
      "can_recur": true,
      "protected": false,
      "biblical_foundation": "Two are better than one - 'If either of them falls down, one can help the other up' (Ecclesiastes 4:9-12)",
      "notes": "Requires coordination with others. Genuine partnership, not transactional meetings. Covenant relationship."
    }
  ]

  // ============================================================================
  // NOTES - Usage Guidelines
  // ============================================================================
  //
  // WHEN TO USE SYSTEM CATEGORIES:
  // - Creating appointments that fit foundational types
  // - Planner logic that handles core appointment behavior
  // - Templates for common Kingdom-aligned scheduling patterns
  //
  // WHEN TO ADD NEW SYSTEM CATEGORIES:
  // - Category proves universally valuable across instances/users
  // - Has biblical or architectural grounding (not just convenient)
  // - Validated in custom categories first (bootstrap pattern)
  //
  // PROMOTION PATH:
  // Custom (testing) → Staging (evaluation) → System (validated)
  //
  // PRIORITY LEVELS:
  // - highest: Sacred, covenant-protected time
  // - high:    Important Kingdom work and renewal
  // - medium:  Valuable but can adapt as needed
  // - low:     Helpful but lowest protection
  //
  // FLEXIBILITY TYPES:
  // - fixed:    Don't move - scheduled time is sacred
  // - flexible: Can adjust within constraints
  // - moveable: Can reschedule as needed
  //
  // ============================================================================

}
